content.description: Start on the right side of the second arete to the right of Legal Dihedral. Either climb straight up past the first bolt that leads out left to the arete along a seam (harder) or traverse in left from the gully (easier). Go up the steep brown, pocketed face to join the arate route route at its fifth (missing at time of FA) bolt.
content.protection: TR from anchors atop righthand (5.10) arete route using two ropes.
content.location: Start on the right side of the second arete to the right of Legal Dihedral.

climbs.name: Legal Dihedral
climbs.fa: P1: Brighton, Rickard, Kronberg, Treiber 1973  P2: O'Kelley, McMahon 1974

content.description: This route climbs an obvious corner system that is to the left (down-canyon) of two striking and bolted aretes. You can rappel after doing the first pitch from the anchor atop the arete that is just to the right of the corner system (5.10+ 5 or more bolts).

Start to the left of Legal Dihedral at a crack system that is just right of two bolted routes (10+ & 9+ and both good). 

  Climb the crack to a rounded arete. Rappel from the top of the bolted climbs to the left.
content.protection: Rappel from the top of the bolted climbs to the left.
content.location: Start to the left of Legal Dihedral at a crack system that is just right of two bolted routes.

content.description: This cliff faces the road and is on the left side as you travel uphill. It is down-canyon of an obvious free-standing pinnacle (The Pope's Penis) that is also on the left (uphill) side of the road.
